f:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates funding rates every hour using a TWAP mechanism that considers the premium between perpetual and spot prices. The on-chain order book ensures transparent rate calculations without centralized manipulation. Funding payments occur automatically through smart contracts, with rates typically ranging from -0.01% to 0.05% per hour depending on market sentiment. The 1-hour frequency provides more granular arbitrage opportunities compared to traditional 8-hour cycles."}]
10:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","DOGE","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"DOGE's high retail interest and social media-driven volatility often create significant funding rate premiums during trending periods. The pair's large trading volume on Hyperliquid ensures sufficient liquidity for meaningful arbitrage positions. Meme coin dynamics frequently lead to sustained directional bias, making DOGE funding rates more predictable than technical analysis-driven assets."}]]}]
11:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"DOGE/USDT funding rates on Hyperliquid have shown distinct patterns correlating with social media sentiment and broader meme coin cycles. During Elon Musk tweets or major announcements, funding rates often spike above 0.1% hourly as retail traders pile into long positions. Conversely, during market downturns, DOGE frequently exhibits negative funding rates as leveraged longs get liquidated. The 1-hour funding frequency captures these rapid sentiment shifts more effectively than traditional exchanges. Weekend periods typically show lower funding volatility due to reduced social media activity and institutional participation."}]]}]
12:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Strategies"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The most profitable DOGE funding arbitrage opportunities on Hyperliquid occur during extreme social sentiment events when funding rates diverge significantly from other exchanges. Traders can capitalize on rate differences between Hyperliquid's 1-hour cycles and Binance's 8-hour funding periods. Delta-neutral strategies work particularly well during high-volatility periods when funding premiums exceed 0.05% hourly. The on-chain nature eliminates counterparty risk while enabling instant settlement. Cross-exchange arbitrage becomes viable when Hyperliquid's rates exceed transaction costs by meaningful margins."}]]}]
13:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Limitations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"DOGE's meme coin volatility can create substantial price risk even in supposedly market-neutral funding arbitrage positions. Hyperliquid's USDC-only collateral requirement means exposure to USDC depeg risk during market stress. The platform's relatively new status compared to established exchanges introduces smart contract and operational risks. Liquidity can become constrained during extreme market events, potentially making position exits difficult. Gas costs on the L1 chain, while minimal, can erode profits from smaller funding rate discrepancies during low-volatility periods."}]]}]
14:["$","$L16",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does Hyperliquid's 1-hour DOGE funding compare to 8-hour cycles?","answer":"Hyperliquid's hourly funding provides more responsive rates to DOGE's rapid sentiment changes. This creates additional arbitrage opportunities but requires more active monitoring. The shorter cycles often result in smaller individual payments but more frequent profit realization opportunities."},{"question":"What makes DOGE funding rates particularly volatile on DEXs?","answer":"DOGE's retail-heavy user base tends to use DEXs for leverage during trending periods, creating imbalanced positioning. The transparent on-chain order book reveals this imbalance more clearly than centralized exchanges. Social media-driven price movements often occur faster than traditional funding mechanisms can adjust."},{"question":"Are there minimum position sizes for DOGE funding arbitrage on Hyperliquid?","answer":"While there's no explicit minimum, profitable arbitrage typically requires positions above $10,000 due to gas costs and spread considerations. The on-chain nature means all transactions are visible, potentially affecting larger arbitrage strategies. Position sizing should account for DOGE's high volatility and potential slippage."},{"question":"How reliable is DOGE liquidity during funding rate spikes?","answer":"DOGE maintains strong liquidity on Hyperliquid during normal conditions, but extreme funding events can strain the order book. The automated market making system helps but may widen spreads during high volatility. Traders should monitor order book depth before executing large funding arbitrage positions."}]}]
